The Patriotic Alliance has jumped in to support arrested Operation Dudula leader, Nhlanhla Lux Dlamini. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Operation Dudula members have asked police not to give their leader Nhlanhla 'Lux' Dlamini any food while he’s in custody. This is as they fear he’ll be poisoned while in prison. Meanwhile, Patriotic Alliance deputy president Kenny Kunene says the charges against Dlamini are preposterous. WATCH | Operation Dudula members clash with police He'll be spending the weekend behind bars following his arrest yesterday. Dlamini has been at the forefront of protests against undocumented foreign nationals.